Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into
half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.
Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Remove @Italian pork sausage mix{9%ounce} from casing if necessary; discard
casing.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add sausage, carrots, and scallion whites; cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add garlic to pot with sausage and veggies; cook, stirring constantly, until
fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{3%cups}, @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, and @chicken stock
concentrates{3}, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pot.

Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a low simmer. Cook until
couscous is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. (You'll add more to the pot in Step 5.)

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Once soup has simmered ~{4-5%minutes}, uncover pot and add broccoli. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove soup from heat; stir in @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon
juice (big squeeze for 4 servings), and as much lemon zest as you like. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and more lemon juice if desired.

Divide soup between bowls and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve.

> Pork Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.